OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: webs
Version: %%VERSION%%
Synopsis: Web server interface to OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2012 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/webs
Description:
 Webs defines a generic and low-level interface between web servers
 and services implemented in OCaml. The connection is mediated
 by a connector. Webs provices CGI and SCGI connectors.
 .
 Webs is made of a single independent module and distributed under the
 BSD3 license.

